column2: Last two weeks we have had heavy rain.  1.5 - 1.75 in a short time.
Hot sunny day.  Lake very calm.
Heavy rain last week and high winds.  Lake up 4".
Worst algae I have ever seen in 3 years we have lived on the lake.
A lot of weeds and slime floating on water.
Rain every day for a week.
Lake was full of seagulls today they must be migrating.
Very high.  Heavy rain and high wind.
Clear.  0.5" of rain on 5/24- 0.6" on 5/25- and 0.4" on 5/26.  The rain gauge reading on 5/23 is 2.50 and 5/25 is 2.54.
Cows in lake again.  Satellite passed over today. 0.3" of rain on 6/21- rain gauge reading for 6/22 is 2.54 and 6/26 is 2.50.
No rain for 23 days.  The satellite passed over today. Rain gauge reading for 6/30 is 2.46- 7/6 is 2.42- 7/12 is 2.38- and on 7/14 is 2.34.
0.4" of rain last night and State Highway Department is taking water from the lake. The rain gauge reading is 2.26.
Satellite passed over today.  Rain gauge reading is 2.28 and on 7/18 had 0.5" of rain.
1.7" of rain on 8/18- 3.6" of rain on 8/01- 0.7" of rain on 8/15- the rain gauge reading for 8/1 is 2.52- 8/15 is 2.38- and 8/20 is 2.48.
Windy. Rain gauge is 2.50 and 1.3" of rain.
Rain gauge reading for 9/9 is 2.62 and 9/7 had 2.5" of rain.
Sunny and calm.  Rain gauge reading for 9/13 is 2.58- 9/21 had 0.2" of rain- and 9/22 had 0.6" of rain.
Satellite passed over today.  Rain gauge reading 2.50.
Rain gauge on May 8 - 2.64- May 9 - 2.70 with 2.9" of rain- May 11 - 2.70 with 0.4" of rain- May 13 - 2.64 with 0.1" of rain.
2 loons.  Rain gauge on May 21 was 2.42 with 0.1" of rain.
Eagle nest on west side of lake.  Rain gauge on May 26 - 2.42 with 0.1" of rain.
Rain gauge on June 2 - 2.40 with 0.9" of rain- June 3 - 2.40- June 4 0.6" of rain- June 7 0.5" of rain- June 9 - 2.42- June 11 0.2" of rain- June 12 - 2.40 with 0.5" of rain- June 16 0.25" of rain.

Rain gauge for June 19 - 2.38 with 0.4" of rain- June 20 0.25" of rain- June 21 0.8" of rain- June 22 - 2.50 with 0.8" of rain- June 23 0.2" of rain- June 24 0.2" of rain- June 25 0.3" of rain- June 27 - 2.48- July 3 0.2" of rain.
Eagle hatched in nest.  Rain gauge for July 8 0.65" of rain- July 10 - 2.42 with 0.10" of rain.
Rain gauge for July 20 - 2.28- July 21 0.8" of rain.
Rain gauge for July 25 0.8" of rain- July 28 0.6" of rain- July 29 0.8" of rain- July 30 - 2.40.
4.4" of rain on August 3- rain gauge on August 5 - 2.82- and rain on 0.10" today.
Rain gauge on August 13 - 2.50- August 15 1.5" of rain- August 18 0.10" of rain- August 20 2.3" of rain.
Rain in September 9=0.2"- 14= 0.3"- 19= 0.1"- 25= 0.6"- 26=0.5".  Rain gauge on September 16 is 2.50.
On 10/21 there was 6" of snow.  Rain in October is 1 = 0.10"- 3 = 1.8"- 8 = 0.4"- 12 = 0.3.  Rain gauge on October 5 is 2.60.
2 swans on lake.  Eagle is back in nest.  Raised one eaglet last year. Ice out 4/13/2003.
2 eagles raised in nest this year.
2" rain on 7/15.  Two young eagles were hatched this year.  4 year old grandson helped.
SAMPLED OVER DEEPEST SPOT NEAR CENTER OF LAKE
Eagle is back on her nest.  Ice out 4/16/2004.
Looks like 2 baby eagles in nest.  Sunny.
DEEPEST SPOT NEAR CENTER OF LAKE
2 loons on lake.  9 days of 90 F + weather.
sunny- calm- green film on water- fine pieces like small hair in water
Not connected to a project; CLMN-033175?
